icy Ramen would be overkill, and you wouldn't be able to enjoy the other flavors of the chicken broth. (this was a little confusing, we thought the $1 extra "topping" hot sauce would be in the soup already, but actually you get a little bowl of hot sauce, we accidently ordered 3 of these, due to the bit of lost in translation with our waiter). OH MY GOODNESS. I took a little sip of the soup...and an amazing explosion happened in my mouth. No more bad mood from the cold, I couldn't stop smiling through my entire meal. The flavors are just absolutely astounding. The noodles are perfectly cooked. The hot sauce is delicious as its own entity. We were eating the hot sauce mixed with white rice because it was just so good. AND to make this bowl of heaven even MORE perfect...TWO pieces of the most melt-in-your mouth delicious Char-siu pork. WOW. Perfectly made. Just fatty enough, just lean enough, just gelatonous enough. I would eat an entire bowl of just this!! We also tried the Grilled Sea Urchin rice bowl which at $5.50 is quite a nice little treat, but...definitely nothing in comparison to the deliciousness of the Spicy Totto Ramen. I don't think I will last more than a week before giving in and heading there again...EVEN with the prospect of having to wait over an hour in the cold! **EDIT** The Spicy Tuna bowl is SO good. The tuna is well seasoned and fresh. Has a very green oniony flavor. If you sit at the bar you get to watch the cooks lovingly craft your bowl of yumminess!
