Different type of ramen broth than I've had elsewhere. Tuesday night 8pm party of 3, and we only had to wait 25m. There was always at least 15-20 people outside waiting in the freezing cold for this. I usually go for tonkotsu ramen, so Totto's was much lighter. They use chicken broth instead of pork broth apparently, and the chicken stock flavor is pretty pronounced. I ordered the Miso ramen with chicken and added spicy bamboo. The broth tasted like a rich chicken stock and then once you mix the miso paste in, it punches it up to make it just right. They give you a huge mound of miso too, so make sure you dissolve it well. The spicy bamboo was just bamboo coated in Japanese chili powder, so it was just ok. Also standard in the dish were curly noodles (thicker than straight noodles and cooked perfectly al dente), half a boiled egg, bean sprouts, scallions, and a little ground pork. They give you a substantial portion of chicken - 3 super thick slices of marinated lean chicken breast (tad dry but the meat was of a good quality). Overall, their ramen is truly satisfying, feels healthier yet still has a good chicken flavor, and doesn't leave you drowning yourself in water to counteract all of the sodium normally in ramen. The noodle boiling guy is also hilarious and incredibly dynamic, so he was entertaining to watch. I still prefer Ippudo over this, but I would definitely come here again for a less sceney, different style ramen night. Also, very small place so parties of over 4 have to split up. Cash only.
